AGI -&nbsp;The Ramadan end party in Turbigo will take place in the sports field of the town, in the area intended for training. It is what the AGI learns in relation to the outcome of the meeting in Prefecture between representatives of the local Muslim community and the administration of the Municipality of Turbigo. On Saturday the Tar of Lombardy had asked the intervention of the Prefect of Milan to settle the dispute between the cultural association 'Moschea Essà&nbsp; and the mayor of Fratelli d'Italia Fabrizio Allevi who had excluded the availability of public spaces to be allocated to the festival. About the hypothesis of the sports field, the first citizen had said that it was not available because the company that has it in management had expressed the concern that it would spoil the grass to the current football season. Other solutions had been excluded complaining of the shortage of staff of the Municipality that would not allow to guarantee the public order.
&nbsp;
"He won the Constitution." Munib Asfaq, spokesman of the Islamic communities of Lombardy, exults after the decision of the Prefect of Milan to guarantee the sports field of Turbigo to the faithful for the celebration of the feast of end Ramadan tomorrow and after tomorrow. "A dozen of our volunteers will guarantee security - says AGI -. We thank the prefect, our lawyers Luca Bauccio and Aldo Russo who have done a great job and all those who have expressed their solidarity in these hard days. We hope that in the future there are no more iron arms with the Municipality, we are ready to cooperate."
&nbsp;
<h2> Prefect, ok also by the mayor
&nbsp;Even the mayor of Fratelli d'Italia Fabrizio Allevi has given his favourable opinion to the identification of the sports field of Turbigo as a space suitable for the party of the end Ramadan. The Prefecture of Milan in a note points out that "to allow the festivities of the religious celebration, has been identified, in agreement with all the parts, the area destined for the workouts of the municipal sports field that, for the presence of a parking area and an adequate perimeter, is suitable for usability and controllability of the spaces".
&nbsp;
You read in the note: "As a result of the decree of the Tar of Lombardy the Prefect of Milan, Claudio Sgaraglia today met the mayor of the Municipality of Turbigo and the cultural association 'Moschea Essa'&nbsp; with the participation of the Questura, the Carabinieri, the Fire Brigade and the Metropolitan City, in order to assess the subsistence of the reasons of safety and public safety for the performance of the next Ramadan holiday. The Mayor has ensured the rapid adoption of the subsequent authorisation and organisational measures. At the end of the meeting, the Prefect Sgaraglia thanked all the parties who, with great spirit of collaboration, allowed the full achievement of the agreement.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
<h2> Prefect, no more than 200 per party
The number of participants at the end of Ramadan in the sports field of Turbigo will not exceed two hundred for security reasons, as indicated by the firefighters. That is what we read in the minutes of understanding between the parties viewed by the AGI. The yes of the Prefecture of Milan arrived also after an inspection of carabinieri and firefighters, charged to assess whether there were the safety conditions that were found. Rejecting the request of the Islamic community, Mayor Fabrizio Allevi had brought public reasons that would not allow the event to take place. The first citizen, read in the document, obtained the free way of the field manager who had not granted it in recent days, according to what he himself reported for fears on the 'tenuta'&nbsp; of the grassy field. The area "is not affected by sporting events in that time slot, is fenced, is capacious and has a parking lot", all conditions that make it the most suitable according to the understanding.

